==English==

===Etymology===
Late Latin [[abacinatus]], past participle of [[abacinare]]; ''ab'' "off" + [[bacinus]] "a [[basin]]".

===Transitive verb===
'''abacinate''' (abacinates, abacinated, abacinating)

# (''[[torture]]'') to [[blind]] by holding a [[red-hot]] metal rod or plate before the eyes<ref>''Webster's Revised Unabridged Dictionary'' (1998, MICRA, Inc.) at [http://dictionary.reference.com/browse/Abacinate dictionary.com]</ref>.

